social_posts.post_text:
Current status. Standing watch while sewing a dress. Definitely a first and certainly the most “productive” passage we’ve had in a while. Next stop, St Martin!

#sewingandsailing #sewingonasailboat #sewing #sailing

Little miss in her new dress. Finished with still an hour left to go in our sail. We are almost there and I am looking forward to a drink! The dress is certainly not perfect, but it is definitely 3-year-old approved!

#sewingandsailing #sewingdresses #sewingonasailboat
French bakeries. No need to say more.

Favorite passage days? The ones that are calm, peaceful, and may or may not involve busting out the sewing machine. Here is a quick recap of our sail the other day and the finished dress for miss Maddie girl. 

#sewingonasailboat #makersgonnamake

Fabric haul in St Martin! I found not one but two fabric stores. Now time to decide what to #sew first!

#sewingonasailboat #makersgonnamake #sewmyownclothes #fabric

How do we stop time to enjoy more of these priceless moments??? This is 3. So much to love about this age and traveling together. 

#travelfamily #thisis3 #slowdowntime

Because sometimes mammas need nights out too. Especially if we are St Barths. And yes, the first picture is a shameless selfie in the bathroom. 

#momsnightout
Made a tortoise friend today.

This is how we grocery shop in the French islands. Especially when we are lucky enough to be with our friends @_everydaysaturday who generously let us go with them on their electric scooters! #roseallday 🍷🥖🧀

When a fabric tells you what it wants to be, you have to listen. Lastest make! #sewingonasailboat #diyclothing 

Also thank you to @sailing_asgard for giving me your old sheet to test the pattern!!!
New island day! Just arrived in St Kitts. What a beautiful entrance. Looking forward to exploring 🥰

As I've been making more of my own clothes and looking for fabric at all of the islands we visit, I've been wondering why I (and all of us) are drawn to some colors more than others. This wild and crazy print needed to come home with me. And that's probably because it has all of my favorite colors in it. When I looked up what the colors meant, I thought .... yup. Sounds about right. You'll notice I didn't include "Navy here" that one said something like "sophisticated, elegant and understated" 🤣

#sewingonasailboat #livethecolorsyoulove
#makeyourownclothes #makersofinstagram
We got a chance to see a Batik artist at work. It was such a fun way to spend the day in St Kitts! #localartist #caribbean #instatravel

Coffee with a view. Thank you to our lovely families for giving us mamas a most special day today!

#mothersdaywithaview
Nevis. ❤️🖤💚💛
Les Saints. Pretty pretty 🥰

Outfits made out of Batik found in St Kitts. 1 of 2. Working on the second one now, but wanted to share Maddie’s sweet new dress!
#sewersofinstagram #diyclothing #batik #sailingfamily #sewingonasailboat

Batik outfit 2 of 2. This one pushed me outside my comfort zone but pretty pleased with how it turned out!

We are still loving our time in Les Saints and the ability to slow down and do as much or as little as we want. I’ve sewn 2 outfits. Read 2 books. Maddie and I each do yoga in the morning and then toddler French videos. Life is calm and easy these days. Next up, Dominica!

 #closetcorepatterns #closetcorecharlie #batik #sewersofinstagram

Happy birthday to my favorite person. 

And thank you @_everydaysaturday for the 📷 and for lending us your daughter to babysit so we could have a nice date night.

This recent make has been staying a little hush hush, but no longer! Meet #notchesbilly the latest pattern from #notches. Last month I got the opportunity to help this amazing new company test this pattern before it went live, and couldn’t love it more. 

Today, it’s finally available for the rest of the world to enjoy! And they are having a 20% off sale this week to celebrate. I’ll add the link on my bio for anyone who wants to check them out. 

#sewingonasailboat #sewersofinstagram #sewyourownclothes #makersgonnamake

It has pockets! Latest make :)
#notches #notchesbilly #sewingonasailboat

Watching these two from a distance never gets old. Nor does Maddie’s clown fish dive bag. 

#girldad #travelfamily #thisis3

Morning fishing hangs. 

#girldad #boatkids #dominica

Maddie “makes friends” with a grey crowned crane. This bird saw her and ran up to the glass to try to peck her. It was pretty cool to see this bird so close and so openly hostile. 

Zoo de Martinique was lovely. A perfect way to spend a couple of hours off the boat enjoying superb gardens and wonderful animals. 

#martinique #travelfamily #naturephotography #greycrownedcrane

How I turn a batik sarong into a beautiful dress. And … how I speed sew to maximize productive time while Maddie naps. 

#sewingonasailboat #sewersofinstagram #diyclothing

Pizza from a vending machine??!! 

#martinique #pizza #vendingmachine

Celebrating this guy today. We love you so. Happy Father’s Day!!

#fathersday #girldad

When in Martinique, you gotta visit some rum distilleries. We’ve been to 2 so far - Saint James and JM. The smell is amazing. The entire grounds smell like sugar. 

#rum #sailingfamily #vlog

There’s a storm a-brewing forcing us to leave Martinique in the morning to head south to Bequia (Vlog update over on TikTok). So it’s time to head out tomorrow. But not before we stock the boat with as much meat and cheese as we can carry. #priorities 

#hurricaneprep #cheese #sailingfamily

Rotten Eggs 🤢 

My first instinct was to throw the lot over board. But eggs are expensive … so Maddie and I cleaned them up and tried to forget the stench of the decayed one. Right choice? I hope so!

#rottenegg #boatlife #sailingfamily

#hurricane update. Bret finally hits us in our safe hole in #grenada. Luckily we and everyone we know are all safe and sound!

#hurricaneseason #sailingfamily #boatlife

I made a new outfit. It’s very bright. And it has pockets. 

#closetcorepatterns #closetcorecharlie #sewingonasailboat #sewersofinstagram #makeyourownclothes

Tonight’s #sunset. One of the best we’ve seen. 

#outdoorliving #sailingfamily #sweetdreams

Latest make for my #mermaidgirl. This one was simple enough, except halfway through i realized my sewing machine had a broken part. I was able to clean the machine and get it to be “usable enough to finish” but I think I’m going to be on a sewing freeze until I can source a new bobbin case from … somewhere. 

Note to any sewing friends thinking they will sew on their boats too. Bring spare parts! I didn’t even KNOW that this part could break, but apparently it’s quite common.

Pattern is #littlelizardking and fabric is from Gaffney’s in Germantown Philadelphia. I use a Singer Heavy Duty sewing machine. Sadly my serger is in storage and not on the boat. You definitely don’t need a serger for bathing suits, but they are better and easier when you have one.

And just like that, we’ve got another fisher girl on our boat! Maddie caught her first, and surely not her last fish today! Next up…spear fishing 😁🎣👯‍♀️

#thisis3 #sailingfamily #letthembelittle

Maddie insisted tonight on wearing our matching bathing suits so we could be “Twinsies”. Then on taking pictures. These are the 3 we got before she ran away. I know she won’t always want me to make her clothes. And definitely won’t always want to match with me. So I’m soaking up every minute of this 3 year old love bug. Even if it’s a struggle to get a decent picture with the two of us these days. 

My suit pattern is from #edgewaterave hers is #littlelizardking 

#sewersofinstagram #diybathingsuit #twinsies

Have you heard of the #manchineeltree? It’s all over here in the Grenadines and the eastern Caribbean. It also happens to be one of the most poisonous trees in the world!

The sap, if it gets on you (particularly if you seek cover under the tree while it’s raining) will burn your skin. The sweet smelling apples will give you a rash I’d you touch them and are very toxic to each. 

So they have become a tree we (and Maddie!) have gotten VERY GOOD at identifying. 

#outdoorliving #sailingfamily #treeidentification

This is what an “errand day” looks like when we are lucky enough to be in a place where we can have access to grocery stores and laundry! 

We absolutely love #carriacou. Great stores, amazing food, suuuuuper friendly people. And laundry. Did I mention laundry??? We did 4 loads and boy, was it a long time coming. 

#sailingfamily #errands #dailyvlog #toddlermom

We thought we had hit the holy grail of cruising… an anchorage to ourselves in the Caribbean. And then this happened 😂😂

#sailingfamily #caribbean #danceparty #ifyoucantbeatemjoinem

People say to us all the time “I could never sail with my kid, they are too crazy”. And maybe that’s true. But nothing entertains a child quite like this incredible playground that nature has given us to explore. And all the sun and warm salt water makes for great naps!

#sailingfamily #letthembelittle #toddlermom

Our Maddie girl. Part 3 year old, other part fish. So proud of this little girl and her love affair with the water. 

We put her in #safetyswimlessons at 18 months and it was the best money we have ever spent. She’s been swimming confidently ever since! Can’t wait to see what the future brings for this “bright and brilliant swimmer”. 

#thisis3 #letthembelittle #littlemermaid

How do we do #datenight while living on a sailboat? Sometimes like this 😂😂😂

So thankful to our friends and the memories we are making together! @_everydaysaturday @svnewworld 

#buddyboating #sailingfamily #igotdressedfornothing

How we #groceryshop in Grenada using the bus system. It’s loud, crowded, cheap, friendly, reliable, and a lot of fun. 

#sailingfamily #everydaylife #travelmore

“How is this going to work”. Thought just before the guys got our broken generator off of our boat. So thankful for friends who being their muscle and engineering minds to help us out! 

#boatproject #sailingfamily #sailinglife

Fixing a floppy sun hat using #zipties 

When to live full-time on a sailboat, you have to get creative with your fixes. We don’t have the ability to just buy a new item every time something breaks, so we make do with the items at hand!

For this project, I used zip ties and hand sewed them into the brim of my son hat. It worked great and I should be able to eek out a bit my life out of this cheapo sun hat :) What other creative uses have you seen for zipties??

#wastenotwantnot #sewingonasailboat #sewersofinstagram #sewing #diy #sailing #sailboatfamily #sunhat

Maddie woke up this morning with a vision. “I want to make a valentine for Daddy”. So she grabbed the bag of “treasures” she collected yesterday at the marina and got to work. 

This is the final product, complete with baby coconuts, a few sticks, a leaf, and a rusty nail. 

We have PBS kids to thank for the idea, and living in the tropics for the treasures. 

#thisis3 #toddlermom #sailingfamily #letthembelittle #artsandcrafts #playcreatelearngrow

Be brave and get #bangs? Sure! Why not. 

Maddie also was brave and got her first ever haircut. Although you wouldn’t notice 😂 she’s still the same ol’ ragamuffin. 

#thisis3 #firsthaircut #toddlermom #sailingfamily #newhairwhodis

Pizza night fail. Who knew Brioche Flour was sweet??? 🤦🏼‍♀️ Guess we’re having pasta …

#dinnerfail #cookingonasailboat #sailingfamily

It’s project time around here. 3 year old princess style. 

#sailingfamily #boatprojects #dressuptime
Paint and sip night sailboat style! Thank you @svnewworld for hosting and providing the 🍷.

Waterfall days. 

We had the place entirely to ourselves. Magical way to spend the morning!

Dads rule. 

This little fish may also turn out to be a little gymnast if we are not careful :)

#girldad #thisis3 #sailingfamily

Let the projects begin! 

Thank you #sailrite for making ordering everything so easy. Getting items to Grenada on the other hand… let’s just say it took a while. But they are here! Let’s get to work. 

#sewingonasailboat #boatprojects

Putting on “real” shoes, and getting all dolled up for the first time in almost a year. 

We are taking a quick boat break to travel around the US visiting friends and family. Last night was Chicago to celebrate our dear friend’s wedding. And have a weekend away with our buddies while Grandma watches the kiddo. 

#datenight #saltycrew

When we visit Grandma, we get to sew and then exclusively wear fancy dresses. 

Pattern is from #violettefieldthreads and fabric from #joannfabrics 

#sewing #homemadeclothes #toddlerdresses

When you sail full time with a 3 year old… boat chores look something like this. 

#sailingfamily #travelfamily #toddlermom #sailinglife #boatkids #boatchores #thisis3 #letthembelittle

Hello from chilly Philadelphia. Back to the boat in T-minus 5 days. Until then, frantically trying to sew enough bathing suits to last me most of the season. 

While I can (and will) make them on the boat, I have a serger sewing machine here that makes sewing bathing suits 💯 easier. Also, if you ever pass through Philadelphia, check out my favorite fabric store Gafneys in Germantown. It’s a local gem!

#diybathingsuit #sewing

Making art with friends in beautiful places. Ticking all the boxes, feeling all the feels. 

#letsmakeart #grenada #buddyboats
Cheers to being back at anchor and the start of our 3rd season on Paradox II.

Community. This is what we have come to appreciate most about sailing as a family. And boy oh boy have we found a wonderful one here on the water. 

Yesterday the moms and the teen girls got together to make art and make bread. Thanks to Amber from @_everydaysaturday for being our bread guru and @sailingexodus for hosting. 

#letsmakeart #sailingfamily #buddyboats #sourdough

She may look just like Will, but she’s my little girl through and through. 

#boatkid #sailingfamily #letthembelittle
We went on a beautiful hike this morning not knowing that it was #nationalhikingday. Petite Martinique is lovely. Even better with friends. @sailingexodus

We challenged Maddie - our 3 year old daughter - to swim by herself from our boat to the beach without any help. This would be her longest swim ever at 200 yards. But with the promise of a Ting if she was successful … she was determined to make it. 

Maddie started to learn how to swim at 18 months with survival swim lessons before we moved into the boat. Now she is certainly part fish. She can dive down to 10 feet and can snorkel calm reefs without us. She’s already asking when she can start spear fishing 😂

This boat kid doesn’t know how to ride a bike… but boy can she swim. 

#boatkid #thisis3 #letthembelittle #sailing #sailingfamily #distanceswimming

social_posts.post_text:
Favorite kinda day. 

#fishon

This is 4!!!!!! Happy birthday little mermaid girl. You are a silly delight who makes friends with any kid you see on the beach, and make us laugh until we cry with your silly songs and stories. Right now your favorite activities include: swimming, diving, putting on ballet recitals, making up songs and singing them at an 11, scootering, and dresses. 

The best thing about this life style, the VERY BEST THING, is that time slows down. We are together all the time making new memories more days than not and even though these last 4 years have gone quickly… they don’t feel like they’ve flown by at the speed that they would have if we were still back in a house with Maddie in day care and us working full time. It just wouldn’t be the same at all. 

Will we do this forever? Probably not. Is it the best thing that we have ever done? Definitely. 

So here are a few photos of now, a candid where I’m clearly trying to keep Maddie small forever, and a few gems from when we started. 

#thisis4 #sailingfamily #boatkids

…and they happen to be our great friends. Way to “Christmas” up the neighborhood @mondaynever !

#christmas #christmaslights #boatfamily #sailing #boatlife #oceanlife #sailinglife #offgridliving #holidayseason #travelfamily #hollyjollychristmas

Martinique photo dump. 

We’ve been pretty quiet here lately. Not because there isn’t anything happening, but because we are enjoying living life off social media at the moment. The past month has been incredible. We’ve settled into the best that Martinique has to offer. From spending 10 days on the windward side in almost complete isolation (it was spectacular, we cannot believe it’s unvisited by cruisers), to birthday dinner at Kube, to friends and more friends and more friends…
It has been a great month. 

Off to points North soon, but the season is still completely up in the air at the moment.
Cat, Will, and Maddie sailing Paradox II, a Contest 46. Documenting our misadventures along the way.
